Recently Weigmann et al., Phys.Rev.C20(1979)115, have
pointed out that a short-range energy dependence of
strength function is not uncommon. Therefore, it is
desirable to extract p-wave strength functions from
average capture cross sections using actual p-wave
For an expression for the average capture cross
sections as a sum of partial cross-sections for
different angular momenta of the incident neutrons,
formula by Bilpuch et al.,Ann.Phys.10(1960)455, was
Assumption that only s- and p-wave neutrons contribute
to the sigma(n,g) at E(n)=24 keV(approx), is used.
s-wave neutron contribution to average sigma(n,g) was
subtracted. The s-wave resonance parameters were used
The p-wave neutron strength are then extracted from
the same formula by Bilpuch et al., using the
experimental values of average p-wave radiation width
